          {
            "commit": "1c91721233da3e0324be8f9154f9592368578b7e",
            "subject": "LU-11553 kernel: new kernel [RHEL7.5 4.14.0-49.13.1.el7a]"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2018-10-30 04:49:04.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2018-10-30 09:21:23.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-11566 utils: increase llog_print buffer size",
        "message": "LU-11566 utils: increase llog_print buffer size\n\nThe current implementation of \"lctl llog_print\" uses a fixed buffer\nsize of MAX_IOC_BUFFER=8192 bytes, and returns the entire config\nin a single buffer.  However, if the configuration is complex, it\nmay overflow the preallocated buffer, which is not handled properly:\n\n    WARNING: PID: 5457 at lib/vsprintf.c:1741 vsnprintf+0x691/0x6a0\n    CPU: 1 PID: 5457 Comm: llog_process_th Kernel: 3.10.0-862.14.4\n    Call Trace:\n     dump_stack+0x19/0x1b\n     warn_slowpath_null+0x1d/0x20\n     vsnprintf+0x691/0x6a0\n     snprintf+0x49/0x70\n     class_config_yaml_output+0x22a/0x430 [obdclass]\n     llog_print_cb+0x415/0x4f0 [obdclass]\n     llog_process_thread+0x892/0x15a0 [obdclass]\n\nThis is not ideal, but it is too late for a proper fix before the\nrelease.  For now, increase the buffer size incrementally to hold\nthe config if possible.\n\nFix the buffer printing to properly detect the overflow case, and\nreturn -EOVERFLOW if the buffer is not large enough, so that the\ncaller can try again.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ibae27df9b7e6c8490e0132484bdeda52963ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
